      <div class="col text">
        <p class="p mt-4 mb-4">Here you can see part of my calculate function that I mentioned above. to start off with I named 
          all of my variables at the top of the calculate function's scope. Then for the calculation the code will find the 
          difference between the two inputs that the user entered. from there the code will run through a series of If/Else 
        statements to find out exactly how many of each denomination to give out. For example, the code will divide the total change 
      due by twenty to find out how many twenty dollar bills to dispense. It  uses the method Math.floor() to return only 
    the whole number bills to give out. After that, the code will redefine the value of the total change due to equal change due minus the value 
  of twenties. The code will hit the else statement if the total change due is less than the denomination and set that 
value to zero before moving on to the smaller denominations.</p>
